<HEADLINE> U.S. Closes Embassy in Ghana After Bomb Threat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The United States embassy and
other U.S. offices in Ghanaian capital Accra have been closed
following a bomb threat, according to a report reaching here
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The report said the U.S. embassy, the consular section,
information services and the U.S. Agency for International
Development were closed Friday and security around the offices
was strengthened after they received information from Nairobi,
saying that Accra would also be a target of terrorism.
</P>
<P>
All staff were turned away when they reported for work and
embassy officials were quoted as saying that they were taking all
threats seriously.
</P>
<P>
A number of countries have received bomb threats following a
massive bomb blast killing over 240 people and injuring more than
5,000 in Kenyan capital Nairobi on Friday last week, the report
added.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright is expected to
visit Kenya and Tanzania this weekend where massive bomb blasts
took place near U.S. embassies in the two capitals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
