<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Earth Crack Creates 4-km-Long Ditch in C. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- An earth crack occurred
last week at Adami Tulu, some 170 kms south of the Ethiopian
capital Addis Ababa, has created a ditch stretching far more than
four kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency Saturday quoted Adugna Urgessa,
vice-chairman of the east Shoa District, as saying that the crack
which resulted from the receding earth in)Ynka Cholmo Farmers
Association is five meters wide and 12 meters deep.
</P>
<P>
Adugna said the crack has been gradually stretching southwards
in the direction of Lakes Abiyata and Shala, two of a chain of
lakes located at the Rift Valley.
</P>
<P>
There is fear that the crack might further widen to join the
lakes which could result in flooding, the local official added.
</P>
<P>
The 2,800 kilometer-long Rift Valley is the longest valley in
the world. This huge and dramatic scar on the face of earth
extends from Lebanon through the Red Sea, down the Danakil
Depression and onwards to form the valleys of Ethiopia and Kenya,
before terminating finally in Tanzania and Mozambique. 
</P>
</TEXT>
