<HEADLINE> Foreigners Evacuated from Kinshasa to Gabon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of foreigners who were
evacuated from the capital of Democratic Republic of Congo,
Kinshasa, will arrive Saturday evening in Libreville, Gabon, on
three or four French Transall military aircraft and a Belgian
Airbus.
</P>
<P>
Agence France-Presse (AFP) reported that a A-310 Airbus
passenger plane sent by the Belgian government carrying about 150
Belgians on board will arrive in Libreville from Kinshasa at 21:00
local time (20:00 GMT).
</P>
<P>
Three or four Transall military aircraft of the French army
will fly some 700 foreigners to Libreville from Brazzaville, where
they arrived Saturday on barges crossing the Congo River from
Kinshasa.
</P>
<P>
Kinshasa is now surrounded by rebel forces who rose against
President Laurent Kabila early this month.
</P>
<P>
A French Airbus plane chartered by the French government is
waiting at the airport of Libreville for a flight to Kinshasa to
evacuate more foreigners who wish to leave Kinshasa.
</P>
<P>
France and Belgium began their evacuation operation Saturday.
</P>
</TEXT>
