<HEADLINE> Youths Arrested for Cutting Rope of Speleologist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Three youths, who are suspected to
have cut a rope installed by a speleologist on the wall of
mountain and thus caused a severe accident, were arrested Friday
at Saint-Jean-de-Maurienne in Savoie in eastern France.
</P>
<P>
A speleologist suffered severe injury from a fall early this
month, when he was using the rope to climb the Alpine mountain,
reported Agence France-Presse (AFP) on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The three youths, aged 18, 19 and 20, were questioned about
their motivation for allegedly cutting the rope and could be
charged with involuntary or voluntary homicide and injury.
</P>
<P>
AFP said that the local youths were angry about the presence of
speleologists.  
</P>
</TEXT>
