<HEADLINE> Syria and EU Sign Aid Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Syria and the European Union
(EU) signed Saturday a framework agreement under which the EU will
provide Syria with loans and technical aid to enhance their
partnership.
</P>
<P>
Syria will receive 65 million U.S. dollars of grants from the
EU and a loan of 250 million U.S. dollars from the European
Investment Bank, in addition to 200 million U.S. dollars worth of
EU technical assistance.
</P>
<P>
The loans will be provided to the Syrian development projects
under the Syrian-EU partnership.
</P>
<P>
The deal, part of the EU investment in the Mediterranean basin
countries, was signed by Syrian Deputy Minister of State for
Planning Tawfiq Ismail with Anrico Toshfi, the EU official in
charge of Asian and the Mediterranean affairs, and Alain Adams,
chief of the mission of the European Commission in Damascus.
</P>
<P>
It came after Syria accepted the EU conditions for providing
financial assistance. Syria has managed to pay its arrears of 306
million dollars to France and of 526 million dollars to the World
Bank in the recent years. 
</P>
