<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The Tunis Stock Exchange continued
its surge in the past week for the third week running, the
market's bulletin said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, the last day of the trading week, the index of the
market closed at 457.5 points Friday, 2.2 points more than the
finish a week ago,
</P>
<P>
The bulletin attributed the index rise to the share boom of
many firms registered at the market.
</P>
<P>
The share price of the Chemicals Company soared by 4.06 percent
to 43.26 dinars (37.62 U.S. dollars), the Tunisian Insurance
Company by 3.81 percent to 13.9 dinars (12.09 dollars) and the
Housing Bank by 1.51 percent to 13.83 dinars (12.03 dollars).
</P>
<P>
While the shares of some firms remained stable, those of
several others declined. They included the Chemical Industry
Company, the Tunisian Capital Investment Corporation, Mesbar
Company, Citax and the Tunisian Arab International Bank.
</P>
<P>
According to the bulletin, the weekly turnover stood at nearly
9.1 million dinars (7.9 million dollars) compared with 8.3
million dinars (7.22 million dollars) in the previous trading
week. 
