<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-four miners were killed,
four others injured in a blast Sunday when methane gas went off at
a coal mine in eastern Ukraine, the Ukrainian Interfax news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred at 12:40 a.m. local time (2140 GMT) 610
meters below ground when 28 miners were working in a pit at the
19th Party Congress mine in the village of Beloye in the Luhansk
region.
</P>
<P>
The four injured miners were rushed to hospital suffering from
extensive burns but their lives were not at risk.
</P>
<P>
The cause was not immediately available and an investigation
team has set off from Kiev to the mine.
</P>
<P>
Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma, on holiday in the Crimea
peninsula, sent a message of sympathy to the families of the
victims.
</P>
<P>
The tragedy brings the death toll in Ukraine's mines to 210
this year, including 63 who died in a similar fire-damp explosion
caused by a spark from a machine last April, the worst mining
disaster in the country since 1985. 
</P>
