reconstruction or modernization now.
</P>
<P>
A Japanese company plans to build a 10 magewatt wind power
plant in west Georgia, which is valued at 10 million
U.S. dollars. Japan's Eximbank will provide 60 percent of the fund
for the project. The European Bank for Reconstruction and
Development will provide 30 percent of fund and the rest will be
financed by a Georgian-Japanese company.
</P>
<P>
