<HEADLINE> Pak Defense Ministry Denies Involvement in Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Ministry of Defense
Sunday denied any involvement of the Pakistan Armed Forces in the
Afghan conflict and expressed its "surprise and anguish" at the
accusation.
</P>
<P>
Terming the accusation as "utterly baseless and mala fide," a
spokesman for the ministry stated in a press release that "no
element or personnel of Pakistan Armed Forces whatsoever were
involved directly or indirectly in the on-going conflict in
Afghanistan."
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Foreign Office had already denied such
allegations vehemently.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the insinuation that Pakistan's 48th Brigade from
Quetta, capital of Balochistan province, was involved in the
Afghan fighting, the spokesman said, "no such formation even
exists in Quetta."
</P>
<P>
"This is absolute rubbish", he remarked. 
</P>
