<HEADLINE> Hot lines Opened for Supervising Flood Donations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Ministry of Civil
Affairs recently established two hot lines dedicated to
supervising the timely and proper handling of donations from
various sources to flood-stricken areas along the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The hot-line numbers are 8610-65229175 during the day and
65135333 at night.
</P>
<P>
The ministry called on local civil affairs departments to
accept supervision from discipline inspection and auditing
departments, media organizations and people handling donations.
</P>
<P>
All donations should be used for flood relief and flood
victims, the ministry stressed, and monetary donations should be
spent on construction of houses for flood victims unless otherwise
designated by donors.
</P>
<P>
Donations should be voluntary, according to the ministry, and
any forms of quota are forbidden.
</P>
<P>
Since August 10, the ministry has received donations valued at
100 million yuan, most of which has been allocated to severely
affected areas. Information on the arrangement of money and relief
goods is available to the public.  
</P>
