<HEADLINE> Henan's Rural Firms Show Stable Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Rural and township enterprises
in central China's Henan Province reported an incremental value of
51.72 billion yuan (6.23 billion US dollars) in the first half of
this year, up 15.1 percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Rural and township enterprises now play a very important role
in Henan, one of China's powerhouses in agricultural economy,
according to experts.
</P>
<P>
Henan's provincial economy is expected to grow by 1 percent for
each increase of 3.8 percentage points for the rural and township
enterprises, the experts said.
</P>
<P>
Official data indicate that Henan had more than 210,270 rural
and township enterprises by the end of last year, the seventh
largest number across the country.  
