<HEADLINE> Espinosa Retains Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHIONGTON, August 16 (Xinhua) -- WBC featherweight titlist
Luisito Espinosa of the Philippines won a controversial
split-decision victory Saturday over challenger Juan Carlos
Ramirez of Mexico in El Pason, Texas, the United States.
</P>
<P>
 The bout was stopped in the 11th round when the two fighters
butted heads.
</P>
<P>
 The fight went to the scorecards and Espinosa retained his
title when two judges had him ahead 105-104 and 106-104. The
third judge had Ramirez on top 106-104.
</P>
<P>
Espinosa built a sizable lead early but got rocked by the
younger challenger late. He was in danger of being knocked out
had the fight not been stopped.
</P>
<P>
Espinosa improved to 43-7. Ramirez, 20, lost for the first
time in 15 bouts.
</P>
<P>
In another fight on the card, Russian-born, Australian-based
Kostya Tszyu dismantled former champion Rafael Ruelas over eight
rounds to earn a shot at the vacant WBC super lightweight title.
</P>
<P>
Tszyu (21-1-1)is now slated to meet Mexico's Miguel Angel
Gonzalez for the WBC title.
</P>
<P>
Ruelas (51-4) lost for the first time since dropping
consecutive bouts in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
