<HEADLINE> Peasants Learn Practical Farming Techniques in Ningxia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Some 800,000 peasants in
northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region have mastered at
least two kinds of practical farming techniques, thanks to a
regional educational campaign.
</P>
<P>
The campaign, launched in September 1990 by the Autonomous
Regional Chinese Communist Party Committee and government, aims to
foster a generation of new farmers who can not only read and
write, but also make money and create better living conditions for
themselves.
</P>
<P>
The hope is that by the year 2,000, more than 400,000
illiterate farmers in the autonomous region between the ages of 15
and 50 will finish their primary education, and that more than 1.1
million young and middle-aged farmers also will be taught at least
two of the practical farming techniques.
</P>
<P>
Since the implementation of the campaign, the illiteracy rate
of the autonomous region's total population dropped from 22
percent in 1990 to 18 percent in 1997, and this rate for young and
middle-aged farmers dropped from 23 percent in 1990 to 9.5 percent
in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
