<HEADLINE> Tourists Arrivals Rise in Tanzania: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Tourist arrivals in
Tanzania reached 359,096 in 1997, a notable increase from 153,000
in 1990, Tanzanian Minister of Natural Resources and Tourism
Zakia Meghji has said.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurating the Tourist Agent License Authority (TALA) at the
weekend in the northern town of Arusha, Meghji said that tourism
earned the country 393 million U.S. Dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
The country is striving to attract 50,000 tourists and turn
tourism sector into the largest foreign exchange earner by the
year 2000, Sunday News quoted the minister as saying.
</P>
<P>
In order to hit the target, the TALA has to exercise full
control of the tourism business, Meghji said.
</P>
<P>
The TALA will operate under the chairmanship of Ambassador
Suleiman Hemed, while the Director of Tourism Salehe Pamba will
be secretary to the board.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Pamba said Tanzania has a total of 200 tourism
companies, 47 percent of which are owned by Tanzanians.
</P>
<P>
The minister also call on tourism companies to provide quality
services to attract more customers. 
</P>
