<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pichler Wins His 11th U.S. Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 15 (Xinhua) -- David Pichler, a member of
the 1996 American Olympic team, won his 11th national title
Saturday at the U.S. Diving national championships.
</P>
<P>
Pichler won the men's 3-meter springboard title with 644.19
points. Defending champion Troy Dumais was forced to withdraw
from the competition with a foot injury.
</P>
<P>
It was the 29-year-old Pichler's first national title on
3-meter.
</P>
<P>
Pichler on Sunday competes on 10-meter platform, his strongest
event. He was sixth on platform at the 1996 Olympic Games in
Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
In the women's 3-meter competition, Michelle Davison won her
first national title with 505.35. Olympic veteran Jenny Keim,
coming off a back injury, was second with 502.23. They were the
only divers to break 500 in the women's final.
</P>
<P>
The six-day selection meet concludes Sunday with the platform
finals for men and women. 
</P>
</TEXT>
