<HEADLINE> Top Hamas Activist Escapes From Palestinian Jail </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian and Israeli troops
have conducted joint searches in and around the West Bank town of
Jericho for a top Hamas member who had escaped from a Palestinian
jail there, it was reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Imad Awadallah, who had been jailed without trial by the
Palestinian National Authority (PNA) since April on suspicion of
shooting dead Hamas master bomb-maker Muhi Sharif, broke out of
his jail on Saturday afternoon, Israeli newspapers said.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian security officials contacted Israel Saturday
evening about Awadallah's escape. Palestinian and Israeli troops
set up roadblocks throughout the West Bank during the search, the
reports said.
</P>
<P>
Awadallah, 29, was considered as one of the top four Hamas
military activists, was arrested in April as a suspect after
Sharif was found dead on March 29 beside a car that blew up in
Ramallah, the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian authorities said Sharif, who was accused by Israel
of masterminding a string of deadly suicide bombings, was killed
in an internal power struggle.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian legislators who have visited Awadallah in jail said
he has denied any connection with the killing.
</P>
<P>
Hamas has accused Israel and the PNA of killing Sharif, but
Israel has denied any role in the death. 
</P>
</TEXT>
