<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cleveland, New York Win in WNBA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The Cleveland Rockers beat
the Washington Mystics 90-71 to clinch their first ever playoff
berth in the WNBA on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
With one game remaining, the Rockers (19-10) hold a half-game
lead over the New York Liberty for first place in the Eastern
Conference. They can capture the conference crown with a win in
their season finale at New York on Monday. The Liberty has two
games remaining.
</P>
<P>
Washington only won three of 28 games this season. Suzie
McConnell-Serio scored a career-high 19 points and Isabelle
Fijalkowski added 17 points and eight rebounds for the Rockers,
who have won 11 of their last 13 games to join Houston as the
only teams to seal postseason spots.
</P>
<P>
McCray and Murriel Page netted 19 points each for Washington.
</P>
<P>
The Liberty improved their playoff chances with a 70-54 win
over the Houston Comets tonight in another game.
</P>
<P>
The Liberty (18-10), who lost by 25 points last month to
Houston, won their fourth straight game to move into a temporary
tie for first place with the Cleveland.
</P>
<P>
The loss was the worst of the year for Houston (25-3) and
snapped a five-game winning streak and nine-game road winning
line for the defending champions.
</P>
<P>
Rebecca Lobo scored 13 points and grabbed 12 rebounds for the
Liberty.
</P>
<P>
In Saturday's last game, Sacramento Monarchs humiliated Utah
Starzz 82-55. 
</P>
</TEXT>
