<HEADLINE> School Girl Upsets Olympic Champ </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Schoolgirl Diana Munz upset
Olympic champion Brooke Bennett in the women's 1,500-meter
freestyle at the U.S. national swimming championships on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 16-year-old Munz clocked 16 minutes, 16 seconds in the non
-Olympic event. Bennett, 18, the 1996 Olympic gold medalist in
the 800 freestyle, was second in 16:20.61.
</P>
<P>
It marked the second time in five days Bennett lost to Munz,
also a winner in the 800 freestyle final on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Other winners on the final night of competition included Tom
Wilkens in the men's 200m individual medley; Olympian Cristina
Teuscher in the women's 200m Individual Medley; Barbara Bedford
in the women's 50m freestyle; Bill Pilczuk in the men's 50m and
Erik Vendt in the 1,500m freestyle. 
