<HEADLINE> Sampras Advances to ATP Championship Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 15 (Xinhua) -- American Pete Sampras moved
within one victory of regaining his world No. 1 ranking Saturday
night when he beat unseeded Magnus Larsson of Sweden to enter the
final of the ATP Championship, a Super 9 event in Cincinnati, the
United States.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, the top seed, claimed the victory 7-5, 2-6, 6-1. He
will battle the fifth seed Patrick Rafter of Australia, who
defeated seventh seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia 7-5, 6-0 in
another semifinal earlier Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"Rafter is the hottest player on tour right now," said
Sampras."But I think I match up well with him."
</P>
<P>
The first set between Sampras and Larsson was tight
throughout,with neither player able to break serve in the first
11 games. "Magnus has a huge game, he's a tough opponent," said
Sampras. "But even after I lost the second set I was pretty
positive about the rest of the match."
</P>
<P>
The 27-year-old Sampras could end Marcelo Rios' one-week
reign if he wins his second straight title at this event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
