<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Application of Science Vital to Flood-fighting Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAICHENG, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Science and technology are
playing a key flood-fighting role in Jilin Province in
northeast China.
</P>
<P>
Severe flooding on the Nenjiang River has raised the water
level of its tributaries to record heights, threatening
several hundred kilometers of dikes in Baicheng City in
northwest Jilin.
</P>
<P>
While inspecting Baicheng, Wang Yunkun, the governor of Jilin,
stressed the application of science and technology in the
flood-fighting efforts.
</P>
<P>
Under the governor's instruction, a great many water
conservancy experts have rushed to the flood-control front line.
</P>
<P>
For example, every 500 meters of the embankment in Tongyu
County is being manned by a water conservancy technician.
</P>
<P>
When a dike in northeastern Baicheng was threatened, about 200
experts and technicians rushed to the scene.
</P>
<P>
The experts have also been sent to help the soldiers who are
fighting the floods.
</P>
<P>
In addition to mechanized equipment, the experts also recommend
the use of iron containers to hold rocks for blocking the water and
the application of plastic films to stop seepage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980816.0094 </DOCNO>
