<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hungary Discovers Arpad Times Tomb </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Hungary discovered a
1000-year-old tomb in the northeast town of Csengersima, The
Hungarian Telegraph Agency reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The discovery of the tomb provides new information to the
Hungarian habitation history.
</P>
<P>
Archaeologists said this tomb of a high historical value
belonged to the Arpad times when the Arpad leader led Hungarians
to settle down here in A.D. 896.
</P>
<P>
The tomb was found by an old couple in Csengersima. Stirrups,
stone figurines and human bones were found in this tomb.
</P>
<P>
This is the second tomb of the Arpad times found Csengersima.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
