<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Ensure Economic Growth Goal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai scored faster economic
growth in July, and is confident of its ability to achieve the
annual GDP growth target of 10 percent, today's China Daily
reported.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai generated 29.84 billion yuan (3.6 billion
U.S. dollars) of GDP last month, a growth of 10.6 percent over the
same period last year, according to Mayor Xu Kuangdi.
</P>
<P>
"We will keep our GDP growing by an extra 0.2 percentage points
in August and September to push the growth rate close to the
target before October 1," Xu said.
</P>
<P>
Growth fell half a percentage point short of the year's target
in the first seven monthes of the year, and the mayor promised to
redouble efforts during the remaining months to attain the set
growth.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is the largest industrial city in China and is a major
equipment supplier to construction projects across the nation. Xu
said that a number of Shanghai manufacturers are preparted to win
orders during the expected nationwide construction boom.
</P>
<P>
He urged local businesses to seek opportunities in large
infrastructure projects and look to out-of-town markets for growth.
</P>
<P>
The mayor also called on government authorities to improve
their own efficiency to facilitate the city's economic growth
targets.  
</P>
</TEXT>
