<HEADLINE> EU Warns Possible Threat From Kosovo to Macedonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) warned
Saturday that the recent armed conflict in the Yugoslav province
of Kosovo might impose a threat to the security of neighboring
Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
Reports from Skopje, capital of Macedonia, said the remarks
were made by Ferhard Jandl, head of an EU delegation at the end of
its two-day visit to Macedonia, which shares 150 kilometers of
common border with Serbia's Kosovo Province.
</P>
<P>
Macedonia would be among the first nations to be affected by an
escalation of the conflict in Kosovo and would receive the
greatest impact, Jandl was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The EU delegation chief held that the Kosovo issue should be
settled as soon as possible, but priority should be placed on the
issue of refugees there.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 200,000 to 300,000 people have been displaced from
their homes and farms in Kosovo since February when fighting began
between ethnic Albanians and Serb police.
</P>
<P>
Jandl also expressed satisfaction with the current stable
situation in Macedonia, saying the nation has set an example for
the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
