<HEADLINE> Peru, Ecuador Hail Troops Disengagement Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Peruvian President Alberto
Fujimori and his Ecuadoran counterpart Jamil Mahuad praised a
recent agreement to disengage troops of the two countries for its
role in avoiding border armed conflicts.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders, meeting in Paraguayan capital of Asuncion on
the sidelines of the inauguration ceremony of President Raul
Cubas, said that the agreement has avoided in a total and
definitive way the possibility of an armed conflict.
</P>
