talks with Ecuador "at the best moment." The two countries fought
a brief and undeclared border war in 1995 for the possession of
Amazonian territory.
</P>
<P>
Talks between Peru and Ecuador to reach a definitive
understanding to end the more than 50 years of border disputes
have been supported by Argentina, Brazil, Chile and the United
States, the four countries that guaranteed the Rio De Janeiro
Protocol.
</P>
<P>
However, the protocol had been discontinued since the end of
last July because of growing tension in the conflict area.
