<HEADLINE> Myanmar Accuses Domestic, Expatriate Organizations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar government has
accused some domestic and expatriate organizations of disrupting
peace and stability of Myanmar by distributing ant-government
leaflets in the country.
</P>
<P>
In a notification to the public carried on Sunday's official
New Light of Myanmar newspaper, the government said domestic
"destructive" group, in collaboration with expatriate groups in
the United States, Thailand and Japan, were distributing
anti-government leaflets to hotels, enterprises and government
departments in the country.
</P>
<P>
