ABSDF (All Burma Students' Democratic Front) -- of being behind
the move aimed at causing panic among the public.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, the Myanmar government also accused four foreign
organizations in the United States, Thailand and the Philippines
of interfering in the internal affairs of the country under the
guise of social work and democracy, and financing the 18 deported
foreigners, who were charged with attempting to incite unrest in
the country. 
