<HEADLINE> Illegal Fishing Causes Nicaragua Big Losses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Illegal fishing and extraction
of maritime products by foreign ships in Nicaragua's territorial
waters have caused the country an estimated annual loss of 25-30
million dollars, a Naval Force officer said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Although illegal fishing is not as rampant as in the previous
years, foreign boats are still engaged in illegal extraction of
marine products, said Naval Force captain Manuel Rivas Guatemala.
</P>
<P>
The limited budgets and naval resources to maintain the
surveillance along both coastlines of the country are the biggest
problem for the Nicaraguan naval force.
</P>
<P>
"We need to remain 30 days in territorial waters with at least
two units," said the officer. 
