<HEADLINE> Guangdong Enjoys Foreign Trade Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 16 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province recorded a total import-export volume of over 74.2
billion US dollars for the first seven months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The figure represented a 6.9 percent increase on the same
period last year, according to the recent statistics released by
the provincial customs office.
</P>
<P>
Exports for the period stood at 43.6 billion US dollars, up 9.2
percent, with imports growing by 3.8 percent to 30.6 billion US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Exports of electronic and mechanical products grew by 14.3
percent on the 1997 period to 18.8 billion US dollars for the
first seven months.
</P>
<P>
During that period, exports to Asian countries grew by 2.3
percent to 24.8 billion US dollars. Exports to Europe shot up by
23 percent, to North America by 15 percent and Africa by 42
percent. 
</P>
