<HEADLINE> Foreign Professionals Help Expand Guangxi Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nanning, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Foreign professionals and
advanced technology are increasingly contributing to the economic
growth of the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region in south China.
</P>
<P>
The region has put in place regulations and favorable policies
to import technologies, equipment, and professionals for local
agriculture and industry. And these policies have produced good
results.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi has so far increased incomes of rural residents by 42.8
million yuan (5.2 million U.S. dollars) by developing their dairy
industry under the guidance of experts from India and Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Widespread application of new rice-planting techniques in dry
areas in 1995, a method imported from Japan, also has helped raise
per-hectare rice output by 716 kilograms, bringing the region an
output increase valued at 387 million yuan. As a result, farmers
have now employed the method over some 1.46 million hectares of
crops this year.
</P>
<P>
A German expert helped solve a technical problem for the
Liuzhou Machinery Factory, bringing the defective-product ratio
down from 3.5 percent to 2 percent.
</P>
<P>
These successes have encouraged the local government to attract
more foreign professionals and technology in a bid to upgrade its
pillar industries. Related departments also are working to
introduce market-oriented personnel systems as part of this
effort, government sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
