<HEADLINE> Five Killed in Italian Highway Landslide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Five people were killed and three
others slightly injured shortly after midnight Saturday when a
landslide crashed onto the Italian side of the Brenner highway
linking Austria and Italy.
</P>
<P>
The five dead were all believed to be foreigners and police
said they did not expect the death toll to rise because its now
clear that no other victims lay under the mud and rocks.
</P>
<P>
Names of the dead would only be known once official
identification was completed, police said.
</P>
<P>
The injured, three Germans, said that they saw a mass of water
and earth hurling toward them down to the mountainside, and they
managed to save themselves by climbing onto the roof of their
camper parked along a side road.
</P>
<P>
The slide, believed to be triggered by a violent rainstorm,
occurred near the town of Fortezza, in the Isarco Valley some 30
kilometers south of the border.
</P>
<P>
The Brenner state highway was reopened to traffic shortly after
the incident, but the expressway and railway line remain closed.
</P>
